           <item row="0" column="1">
            <widget class="QLabel" name="label_18">
             <property name="text">
              <string>When an interface object is created as a child object of another interface, FirewallFabrik can verify that the name and type of the child and parent objects match and form valid configuration. It can also automatically guess some interface types and parameters using their names. For example, it can set the interface type to &quot;vlan&quot; and assign a VLAN ID if the name looks like a valid VLAN interface for the given OS. In some situations the desired configuration might be more complex than these checks allow, so this may need to be turned off.</string>
             </property>
